{
  "texts": [
    "In computer graphics and CAD applications, 3D objects are often stored using polygon meshes.",
    "This representation technique is slightly more complex than other types, such as depth images or point clouds, but the relationships of the edges, faces, and vertices are well-defined, and therefore the complex objects are stored with high accuracy.",
    "This well-defined nature of a mesh makes the objects easily deformable by applying a transformation on a given vertex or edge.",
    "Fig. 4 The taxonomy of this survey.",
    "The first level represents the 4 major data type categories, while the next level refers to the application domains"
  ]
}